## Multithreading with CPU Visualization

### Each Thread Gets Its Own Stack
```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 JVM Memory               │
│                                          │
│  Thread 1 Stack   Thread 2 Stack         │
│  ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────┐          │
│  │ ref → ●──┼─┐ ┌─┼── ref   │          │
│  │ local var│ │ │ │ local var│          │
│  └──────────┘ │ │ └──────────┘          │
│               ↓ ↓                        │
│          ┌─────────────┐                 │
│          │  HEAP (RAM) │                 │
│          │  ┌────────┐ │                 │
│          │  │ Object │ │  ← SHARED!     │
│          │  └────────┘ │                 │
│          └─────────────┘                 │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```
> Both threads share the SAME heap object — this is where problems like race conditions begin!

### Race Condition Example
```
counter = 0  (in Heap)

Thread 1 (Core 1)         Thread 2 (Core 2)
──────────────────         ────────────────
read counter → 0           read counter → 0
add 1                      add 1
write counter = 1          write counter = 1
                           ❌ Expected 2, got 1!
```

### Fix with Synchronized
```
Thread 1                    Thread 2
────────                    ────────
🔒 Lock acquired            ⏳ Waiting...
read counter = 0
add 1
write counter = 1
🔓 Lock released
                            🔒 Lock acquired
                            read counter = 1
                            add 1
                            write counter = 2
                            🔓 Lock released
✅ Result = 2  Correct!
```

### CPU Cache Visibility Problem
```
Core 1                          Core 2
──────                          ──────
L1 Cache: counter = 1           L1 Cache: counter = 0
      ↕                               ↕
         RAM (Heap): counter = 1

Core 2 has STALE data in cache! ❌
Fix → use volatile keyword
```

```java
volatile int counter = 0;
// Forces CPU to always read/write from RAM
// Ensures visibility across all cores
```

