## How Many Processes & Threads in a Java Program?

### Simple Answer
```
You run:  java HelloWorld

Processes created = 1  (JVM process)
Threads created   = 6+ (JVM default threads)
YOUR threads      = 1  (main thread only)
```

### The JVM Process Creation
```
You type: java HelloWorld.java
               ↓
Step 1: OS creates a NEW PROCESS for JVM
               ↓
Step 2: JVM starts inside that process
               ↓
Step 3: JVM sets up memory layout
               ↓
Step 4: Class loader loads HelloWorld.class
               ↓
Step 5: JVM creates "main" thread
               ↓
Step 6: main thread runs your code
               ↓
Step 7: program ends → JVM process destroyed
```

### Default JVM Threads (Auto-created)
```
┌────┬──────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┐
│ ID │ Thread Name          │ Purpose                    │
├────┼──────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
│ 1  │ main                 │ runs YOUR code             │
│ 2  │ Reference Handler    │ cleans weak references     │
│ 3  │ Finalizer            │ runs finalize() before GC  │
│ 4  │ Signal Dispatcher    │ handles OS signals (Ctrl+C)│
│ 5  │ Attach Listener      │ for JVisualVM tools        │
│ 6  │ Common-Cleaner       │ modern GC helper           │
└────┴──────────────────────┴────────────────────────────┘

You wrote 0 threads → JVM created 6 automatically!
```

### JVM Threads vs YOUR Threads
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                JVM PROCESS                      │
│                                                 │
│  JVM Internal Threads (work for JVM)            │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │ Reference Handler  → manages memory     │   │
│  │ Finalizer          → cleans objects     │   │
│  │ Signal Dispatcher  → handles Ctrl+C     │   │
│  │ GC Thread          → garbage collection │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                                                 │
│  YOUR Threads (work for YOUR program)           │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │ main thread        → your code          │   │
│  │ Thread 1           → download file      │   │
│  │ Thread 2           → send email         │   │
│  │ Thread 3           → process payment    │   │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Java Code to Verify
```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println("My PID: "
            + ProcessHandle.current().pid());

        System.out.println("Thread count: "
            + Thread.activeCount());

        Thread.getAllStackTraces()
              .keySet()
              .forEach(t -> System.out.println(
                  "Thread: " + t.getName()
                + " | State: " + t.getState()
              ));

        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
}
```

