## Why Do We Need Multithreading?

### Problem Without Multithreading
```
Single Thread — Sequential Execution:

[downloadFile 5s] → [sendEmail 3s] → [payment 4s]
                                      = 12s total 😴
```

### Solution With Multithreading
```
Multi Thread — Parallel Execution:

Thread1: [downloadFile  5s        ]
Thread2: [sendEmail 3s  ]
Thread3: [payment    4s    ]
                            = 5s total ✅
```

### Real World Examples

#### Web Server
```
Without Multithreading ❌
──────────────────────
User 1 request → processing...
                    User 2 WAITS
                    User 3 WAITS

With Multithreading ✅
─────────────────────
User 1 → Thread 1 → processing
User 2 → Thread 2 → processing
User 3 → Thread 3 → processing
```

#### Video Player
```
Without Multithreading ❌         With Multithreading ✅
─────────────────────────         ───────────────────────
Main thread decodes video →       Thread 1 → decode video
no time for audio!                Thread 2 → play audio
UI freezes!                       Thread 3 → handle UI
                                  Thread 4 → buffer data
```

#### Food Delivery App
```
Without Multithreading ❌
Fetch restaurants → 2s
Fetch location    → 1s
Fetch offers      → 1s
Fetch orders      → 1s
               Total = 5s 😴

With Multithreading ✅
All 4 fetches happen TOGETHER = 2s only! 🚀
```

### When to Use Multithreading
```
✅ Use when:
→ Tasks are INDEPENDENT
→ Tasks involve WAITING (network, file, DB)
→ Heavy computation to split
→ UI must stay RESPONSIVE

❌ Don't use when:
→ Tasks depend on each other's result
→ Very simple/fast program
→ Tasks share data heavily
```

