## Concurrency vs Parallelism

### Single Core — Concurrency (Not truly simultaneous)
```
Core 1 only
─────────────────────────────────────────────→ time

Thread 1 ████░░░░████░░░░████░░░░
Thread 2 ░░░░████░░░░████░░░░████
Thread 3 ░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░████░░░░

█ = running    ░ = waiting

Only ONE thread runs at a time!
CPU switches so fast it FEELS simultaneous
This is called → CONTEXT SWITCHING
```

### Multi Core — True Parallelism
```
Core 1  → Thread 1 ████████████████████
Core 2  → Thread 2 ████████████████████
Core 3  → Thread 3 ████████████████████
Core 4  → Thread 4 ████████████████████

All running at EXACTLY the same time! ✅
```

### Context Switching
```
Thread 1 running...
      ↓
Timer Interrupt fires! (every ~1-10ms)
      ↓
OS Scheduler steps in
      ↓
Save Thread 1 state (registers, program counter, stack) → PCB
      ↓
Load Thread 2 state from PCB
      ↓
Thread 2 runs...
```
> PCB = Process Control Block — OS saves thread state here

### Analogy
```
CONCURRENCY (1 core)              PARALLELISM (multi core)
════════════════════              ═════════════════════════
One chef cooking 3 dishes         Three chefs cooking 3 dishes
Switches between tasks quickly    Each chef works independently
Feels like doing all at once!     Truly happening at same time!
```

### Summary Table
| | Single Core | Multi Core |
|---|---|---|
| **Type** | Concurrency | Parallelism |
| **Truly simultaneous?** | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| **How?** | Context switching | Each core runs a thread |
| **Feels simultaneous?** | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |

